	(uuid "6293f612-ad61-4760-ad66-c804a0624dd1")
	(paper "A4")
	(lib_symbols)
	(text "Animation Platter\n\nThis project is inspired by zoatropes. \n\nA BLDC motor or a NEMA17 stepper motor is used to spin an \nanimation platter. Above the animation platter is an array of\nmany bright LEDs. the LEDs provide the \"stroboscopic effect\" by\nstrobing the lights at a frequency based on the frame count on\nanimation platter.\n\nThe BLDC motor is driven with a standard hobby grade BLDC driver.\nThe communicaiton output is PWM. Using a BLDC motor allows for \nmuch higher speeds. The communcation interface is 5V. Motor voltage\nis 12V\n\nThe NEMA17 is driven by a TMC2209 silent stepper driver. The \ndriver is controlled through GPIO pins only.\n\nThe LEDs are driven by a mosfet. The output connector is supplied \nwith +12V supplied by VR1. There is also a neopixel output that\ncan be used for the strobe lights. The connector extends the \nneopixel line that already exists on the PCB.\n\nThe microcontroller on board is a STM32H7A3RIT. This is a high\nperformance microcontroller running @250MHz. This allows driving\nmultiple full color LCDs while having several pulse sequences \npatterns and multiple external sensors. The microcontroller is \nrich in timers, DMA, memory and speed.\n\nInterfacing with the system is done with three toggle switches,\nan encoder with a button, a potentiometer and two button. Status\nis indicated with four NeoPixel LEDs and two full color LCD displays."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
